claim: Flublok contains 3x the hemagglutinin (HA) antigen content of standard-dose flu vaccines, which has been linked to greater immunogenicity vs standard-dose flu vaccines.
explanation: Multi-panel figure showing ELISA antibody titers (Log2 scale) to egg-derived and cell-derived HA antigens at Day 0 and 1 month post-vaccination for different vaccine combinations, geometric mean ratios of egg/cell HA ELISA titers, and stalk-specific ELISA titers and fold-rises for H3 and H1 stalks across the same vaccine groups. The figure presents comparative immunogenicity (ELISA titers and fold-rises) among vaccine groups but does not report HA antigen content or indicate a 3× HA dose in Flublok; therefore, it does not support the claim. Note: Image panels are small and some labeling is condensed, but antigen dose information is clearly not shown.
